# Backend Lifecycle

When you start the .NET backend (`dotnet run` on the API project), you **must** shut it down before ending your turn. Track the PID from the startup output and `taskkill /PID <pid> /F` when done.

- Never leave the backend running in the background after your work is complete.
- If you started it only to verify endpoints or test a fix, kill it immediately after confirming.
- If the user needs it running for ongoing development, tell them the PID so they can manage it themselves.
